help.auto-scale-chart: If true, the chart's y-Axis starting value is automatically calculated. If false, the chart's y-Axis will always start at zero.
help.chart-legend-position: The position of the legend relative to the chart.
help.elimination-explanation: Select an optional variable for each classification to be marked as the Elimination variable. Elimination identifies the aggregate variable (e.g. Total, All, State) for the purposes of a default selection or computing averages such as percentages.
help.fluid-time: Maintain the same time pattern when new timepoints get published, e.g. always display the last 5 time points.
help.map-explanation: Select an optional Map against geographical Classifications. This enables plotting the dataset on a map.
help.save-query: Add to your Saved Queries to quickly re-run again.
help.sort-chart: Sort the order of the variables by value.
help.stacked-chart: Stack each series to show comparisons between data.
help.stacked-chart-percent: Stack each series as a percentage to show comparisons between data.
help.widget-copyright: Add the copyright to the widget.
help.widget-link: Add the link to the data source to the widget.
help.widget-map-borders: Add boundary borders to the map.
help.widget-map-colour-scale: Choose a choropleth colour scale for the map.
help.widget-title: Add the table title to the widget.
help.widget-responsive: Automatically adapt the widget for different screen sizes.
help.redundant-columns: Show all columns, even if all variables are the same.
help.x-axis-max-steps-chart: The maximum number of ticks and gridlines to show on the x-Axis
